    "summary": [
      "The Paris Agreement, adopted on December 12, 2015, aims to limit global warming to 1.5°C, but current temperatures are nearing this threshold, according to the IPCC's Sixth Assessment Report.",
      "Global CO₂ emissions reached a record 37.4 gigatons in 2023, despite progress in renewable energy adoption by countries like Germany, China, and the United States.",
      "The European Union has reduced emissions by 32% since 1990 under the European Green Deal, while Brazil faces criticism for deforestation rates of 11,568 km² in 2024, as reported by INPE.",
      "Fossil fuel companies spent $750 million lobbying against climate legislation between 2020 and 2024, according to a report by InfluenceMap, while renewable energy capacity continues to grow globally."
